{
  "texts": [
    "Single-nucleus RNA-seq data filtering, normalization and clustering analysis.",
    "We used the R package Seurat (version 3.0) 60 to process gene expression count matrices.",
    "We first applied SCTransform to normalize molecular counts, scale and identify variable genes 25.",
    "After manual inspection we applied per sample minimum and maximum thresholds on the number of detected genes in a given nucleus to exclude both nuclei with low RNA content and potential doublets (sn_H1: >150 and <1700 detected genes; sn_H3: >200 and <2000 genes; sn_H4: >70 and <1100; sn_R2: and sn_E2: >150 and <1200 genes).",
    "In addition, we excluded nuclei with more than 10% of UMIs aligning to mitochondrial genes."
  ]
}